sql:
SELECT pitcher_name
FROM pitchers
WHERE era < 3.00;

SELECT COUNT(*) AS left_handed_pitchers
FROM pitchers
WHERE handedness = 'left';

SELECT pitcher_name
FROM pitchers
WHERE wins = (SELECT MAX(wins) FROM pitchers);

SELECT pitcher_name
FROM pitchers
WHERE era = (SELECT MIN(era) FROM pitchers);

SELECT pitcher_name
FROM pitchers
WHERE pitcher_id = 0;

external_knowledge:
ERA (Earned Run Average) is a measure of a pitcher's average number of earned runs allowed per nine innings pitched; A lower ERA indicates better performance.; 
WHIP (Walks plus Hits per Innings Pitched) measures the average number of walks and hits a pitcher allows per inning pitched; A lower WHIP indicates better performance; 
Strikeouts are an important aspect of a pitcher's performance, with more strikeouts generally indicating better performance; 
Ranking pitchers based on these three criteria provides a comprehensive assessment of their performance.

sql:
SELECT pitcher_id, ip, er, so
FROM pitching_stats
WHERE game_id = 0;

external_knowledge:
- The most recent season is determined by the highest season ID; 
- A higher average innings pitched indicates a pitcher who pitches more innings per game on average; 
- A lower ERA indicates a more effective pitcher, as it represents the average number of earned runs a pitcher allows per nine innings pitched.

